$ !SASROOT/utilities/bin/sasauth

`sasauth` performs authentication. It supports system authentication (such as → Linux/fhs/etc/passwd), LDAP repositories and
→ development/security/authentication/Pluggable-Authentication-Modules[PAM authentication].

`sasauth` is configured via → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/utilities/bin/sasauth_conf

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/utilities/bin
